gather()

use gather to turn gap_wide into a long format dataset

gap_long<-gapwide %>% 
  gather(key = obstype_year, 
         value = obs_values,
         dplyr::starts_with("pop"),
         dplyr::starts_with("lifeExp"),
         dplyr::starts_with("gdpPercap"))

the :: indicate that starts_with comes from the dplyr package

gap_long<-gapwide %>% 
  gather(key=obstype_year, 
         value = obs_values,
         -continent, -country)

separate out the year

gap_long <- gapwide %>% 
  gather(key = obstype_year,
         value=obs_values,
         -continent, -country) %>% 
  separate(obstype_year,
           into = c("obs_type","year"),
           sep = "_",
           convert=T)

plot long format data

life_df <- gap_long %>% 
  filter(obs_type=="lifeExp",
         continent == "Americas")
head(life_df)
## # A tibble: 6 x 5
##   continent   country obs_type  year obs_values

ggplot(data=life_df,aes(x=year,y=obs_values, color=country)) +
  geom_line()
